  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "GnqaMbIUCzA11yVRUBfGTCpuC8M=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nEvery reactor `IChannel` implementation exposes three `IMailbox` instances \u2014 `inbox`, `outbox`, and `deadLetter` \u2014 plus lifecycle and connection-state APIs.\n\n## Interface (from source)\n```typescript\ninterface IChannel {\n  inbox: IMailbox;        // Ops received from remote\n  outbox: IMailbox;       // Ops to send to remote\n  deadLetter: IMailbox;   // Failed ops\n  init(): Promise<void>;\n  shutdown(): Promise<void>;\n  getConnectionState(): ConnectionStateSnapshot;\n  onConnectionStateChange(callback): () => void;\n}\n```\n\n## Why this shape\n- Uniform contract lets SyncManager treat GQL, Swarm, or any future channel identically.\n- `deadLetter` is a first-class concept, not an afterthought \u2014 failed ops are observable and retryable.\n- Connection state is part of the interface, enabling UI-level channel health without channel-specific code.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"Key Types\" section.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:42.000Z"
    }
  },
